[[!tag Energy_Drink Review]]

Vitaminwater is one of those brands I typically ignore, along with all other
"health" branded drinks, because I normally get my [daily
dose](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dQw4w9WgXcQ) of vitamins and minerals from
my diet.

But this isn't just normal Vitaminwater though. And it's not really an energy
drink either, but it _does_ have 60mg of caffeine and has _energy_ in the title.
This flavor, Energy Tropical Citrus has been on shelves since at least 2002[^1].
Some sources I've seen list the caffeine content at 50mg but the bottle I have
in my hands says 60mg. They probably adjusted it some time between release and
now. Not that a difference of 10mg is perceptible, but it does push the drink to
being equivalent to about half a 12oz [[Red_Bull]].

